import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react' import '../styles/NewSession2.css' const NewSession2 = ({API_URL, onShow, session, setSession, exercisesSession, setExercisesSession, exercises}) => { const emptyExercise = { exerciseId: 0, name: '', series: 0, minReps: 0, maxReps: 0, rest: 0, RIR: 0, observations: '' } const handleSession = (key, value) => { let updated = {...session} updated[key] = value setSession(updated) } const handleExerciseSession = (key, value, i) => { let updated = [...exercisesSession] updated[i][key] = value setExercisesSession(updated) } const removeExerciseSession = (i) => { let updated = [...exercisesSession] updated.splice(i, 1) setExercisesSession(updated) } const addExerciseSession = (e) => { e.preventDefault() let updated = [...exercisesSession] updated.push(emptyExercise) setExercisesSession(updated) } const handleClick = () => { console.log(exercisesSession) } useEffect(() => { }, [API_URL, onShow]) return (
handleSession('name', e.target.value)} />
